Diagram a Simple ETL Pipeline (No Execution)
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of databases and data concepts
Familiarity with Linux command line
Text editor experience (nano, vim, or gedit)
Understanding of what data sources and destinations are
Learning Objectives
By the end of this lab, you will be able to:

Identify components of an ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) pipeline
Design a basic ETL architecture diagram
Explain data flow between pipeline components
Document transformation requirements
Create visual representations of data pipelines
Introduction
ETL (Extract, Transform, Load) pipelines are fundamental to data engineering. Before building pipelines, you must design them. This lab teaches you to diagram a simple ETL pipeline for a real-world scenario: processing customer order data from a CSV file into a database.

Scenario: An e-commerce company receives daily order files in CSV format. You need to design a pipeline that extracts this data, transforms it (cleans and enriches), and loads it into a PostgreSQL database for analysis.

